25|$|In 1940 the Kirov Ballet {{once again}} {{made plans to}} revive La <b>Bayadère,</b> this time in a staging by the Balletmaster Vladimir Ponomarev and the Premier danseur Vakhtang Chabukiani. This version would be the {{definitive}} staging of La <b>Bayadère</b> from which nearly every subsequent production would be based. The Ponomarev/Chabukiani revival of La <b>Bayadère</b> premiered on February 10, 1941 to a resounding success, with Natalia Dudinskaya as Nikiya and Vakhtang Chabukiani as Solor.|$|E
