25|$|Les <b>bayadères</b> is {{an opera}} in three acts by the {{composer}} Charles-Simon Catel. The French-language libretto, by Victor-Joseph Étienne de Jouy, {{is based on}} Voltaire's story L'education d'un prince. It was first performed at the Paris Opéra on 8 August 1810 with the famous soprano Caroline Branchu in the lead role of Laméa. Les <b>bayadères</b> was Catel's most popular opera.|$|R
